<br>
First off, after 6 months, you'll have a significant part of the population in the lvl 50 bracket anyways.  <br>
<br>
Second, the one character per account option would be something of a barrier to entry for most people.  <br>
<br>
Third, this server is so scarcely populated as it is, even if 50% of the people brought in another account, the population would still be far below the other production servers.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the whole &quot;allowing strangers inot a community&quot; thing is not really valid.  Who will actually associate with the new transferred character other than the player's particular group and guild.  Really, what is the difference between the transfer and a guild uber pling a character from scratch to 50 in 3 days?<br>
<br>
Fifth, I miss my necromancer /cry /pine /mourn!<br>
<br>
Personally I wish they'd allow transfers to this server...that way a certain necromancer could sacrifice a certain noodle-armed paladin to his heart's content.<br>
<br>
Rexfelix<br>
